The paper deals with the design and optimization of a multiuser massive MIMO downlink system with low-cost, low-bitrate terminals and sensors, which is a topic that falls under the intersection of several CS sub-fields. However, the focus on waveform design, optimization, and detection aspects suggests that the paper is most likely to belong to the Information Theory (cs.IT) sub-category. Other relevant sub-categories include Networking and Internet Architecture (cs.NI), Systems and Control (cs.SY), Multimedia (cs.MM), and Machine Learning (cs.LG), as the paper touches upon aspects related to spatial channel precoding, low-complexity IoT networks, and optimization techniques.
